  "name": "1 Corinthians 3:10–23",
  "localizedName": "1 Corinthians 3:10–23",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Believers who share the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108043",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "good news"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " about Jesus are builders for God. That is how Paul described them. When they tell people about Jesus, it’s like they lay the foundation for the building. Paul did this for the Corinthian church."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Paul asked the Corinthians what they were building on the foundation he had laid. He was talking about how they were putting their faith into practice. God will test and judge what people think and what they do. Teachings about Jesus that aren’t true will burn like a building that catches on fire. "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108208",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Work"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " that isn’t based on God’s Spirit will also burn up. What is true and based on Jesus will last on "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108055",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "judgement day"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". It will be blessed by God."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {},
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Paul wanted the Corinthians to be like the wise builders that Jesus taught about in Matthew 7:24–29. Wise builders listen to Jesus and obey him. Foolish builders follow their own ideas or those of other human teachers. The building that Paul talked about was the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108417",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "temple"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Jesus is the foundation. Jesus’ followers are the building itself. The Holy Spirit lives among them. This is a picture of how God is present on earth through believers."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
